column1: #Text=Douala is the largest city and the commercial centre of Cameroon .
#Text=Serves as the main entrance point in the country .
#Text=Camair-Co ( national carrier ) is the main service provider to the city of Douala .
#Text=Other airlines also fly to Europe - Air France ( Paris ) , Royal Air Maroc ( Morocco ) , Brussels Airlines ( Brussels ) and Turkish Airlines ( Istanbul ) .
#Text=Several airlines provide links to African destinations .
#Text=Flights to Douala with major airlines are not available daily , hence a flexible schedule and a timely reservation is required .
#Text=On flights out of Douala a cash-only airport tax of FCFA 10 000 is payable after you have checked in but before passport control .
#Text=There are several daily services from the capital Yaoundé , brand new Intercity trains takes 3:45 h to complete the journey .
#Text=There 's also a slower service from Kumba twice a week .
#Text=The central station in Douala , ( Gare de Bessengue ) is located just off Blvd. de la Réunification .
#Text=The Route Nationale 3 ( N3 ) from Yaoundé to Limbe and the Route Nationale 5 ( N5 ) from Bafoussam to Douala are the two main roads linking Douala to other cities of the country .
#Text=There are passenger ferries , usually one sailing per week , from Bata and Malabo , both located in Equatorial Guinea .
#Text=Museum showcasing the rich maritime history of Douala .
#Text=Douala Memorials , Douala water park , Douala shops
#Text=have ten Master card / visa card ATMs all over Douala
#Text=Ibis Hotel , Vallée des Princes Hotel , The Douala Gingerbrook Hotel , Halmari Hotel , Karkson Hotel , Borduav Hotel , Veavousa Hotel
#Text=Planet Hotel , Akwa , west of the city , ☏ +23733433131 .
#Text=Modern and marginally maintained hotel which is convenient for airport .
#Text=Wireless internet works well , air conditioners do not .
#Text=Rooms are generally clean and have TV with a few English channels .
#Text=If you need entertainment , there is a nightclub across the street .
#Text=Peninsula Plaza Hotel , Voie Makepe Est ( North side of the city ) , ☏ +2373471741 .
#Text=A modern hotel which is on the northern side of the city .
#Text=Rooms are quite good , with air conditioning .
#Text=Internet might not work and hot water from in room boiler may not work .
#Text=Hôtel Akwa Palace , 920 Boulevard de la Liberté .
#Text=English and French language broadcasts can be heard on BBC World Service on 101.3MHz .
#Text=British Honorary Consulate , BP 1016 Douala , ☏ +23733439732 , fax : +23733439732 , ✉ Constance.Njike-HonCon@fconet.fco.gov.uk .
